@page "/policies/terms-and-conditions"
@layout KioskLayout
@using NewHeights.TimeClock.Shared.Constants
@attribute [AllowAnonymous]

<PageTitle>SMS Terms and Conditions - @AppConstants.Branding.ShortName</PageTitle>

<div class="policy-page">
    <div class="policy-sheet">

        <header class="policy-masthead">
            <div class="policy-logo">
                <img src="/images/logo.jpg" alt="New Heights" class="policy-logo-img" />
            </div>
            <div class="policy-title-block">
                <h1>NEW HEIGHTS</h1>
                <p class="policy-subtitle">Adult High School | Administrative Offices</p>
            </div>
        </header>

        <div class="masthead-rule"></div>

        <table class="policy-meta" role="presentation">
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td class="meta-key">Policy Title:</td>
                    <td class="meta-val">SMS Terms and Conditions</td>
                    <td class="meta-key">Department:</td>
                    <td class="meta-val">Human Resources</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class="meta-key">Effective Date:</td>
                    <td class="meta-val">April 17, 2026</td>
                    <td class="meta-key">Policy ID:</td>
                    <td class="meta-val">NH-SMS-002</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td class="meta-key">Contact:</td>
                    <td class="meta-val">Campus Manager / HR</td>
                    <td class="meta-key">Revision Number:</td>
                    <td class="meta-val">0</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>

        <h2 class="policy-h1">TERMS AND CONDITIONS</h2>
        <div class="policy-description-box">
            <strong>NEW HEIGHTS SMS PROGRAM &mdash; TERMS AND CONDITIONS</strong>
        </div>

        <h2 class="policy-h1">PROGRAM DESCRIPTION</h2>
        <p>
            New Heights Adult High School ("New Heights," "we," "us," or "our") operates an
            internal SMS notification program that (1) notifies approximately 13 substitute
            teachers of day-of assignment opportunities with accept/decline links, sends
            confirmation messages after acceptance, and (2) alerts all staff of emergency
            situations such as weather closings and campus safety events. This program is
            <strong>not a consumer marketing program</strong> and is available only to current
            employees of the district.
        </p>

        <h2 class="policy-h1">CONSENT</h2>
        <p>
            Consent to receive SMS from New Heights is captured during employee onboarding
            as part of the signed Staff Handbook Acknowledgment (see Policy NH-SMS-001 &mdash;
            SMS Notification Consent). The public cannot opt in to this program. By providing
            a mobile number to Human Resources and signing the acknowledgment, you consent
            to receive SMS at that number for the purposes described above.
        </p>

        <h2 class="policy-h1">MESSAGE FREQUENCY</h2>
        <p>
            Message frequency varies based on district operations. Substitute-roster recipients
            may receive 0&ndash;10 messages per month during the school year. All-staff emergency
            notifications are infrequent and sent only as needed.
        </p>

        <h2 class="policy-h1">COSTS &mdash; MESSAGE AND DATA RATES</h2>
        <p>
            <strong>Message and data rates may apply</strong> according to your mobile carrier
            plan. New Heights Adult High School does not charge you to receive messages. Carriers
            are not liable for delayed or undelivered messages.
        </p>

        <h2 class="policy-h1">OPT-OUT (STOP)</h2>
        <p>
            You may opt out of SMS at any time by replying <strong>STOP</strong> to any message
            from our toll-free number. You will receive a single confirmation that you have been
            unsubscribed, after which you will not receive further SMS from the program. You may
            also contact Human Resources directly to be removed. Opting out of SMS does not
            affect your employment and does not remove you from email communications.
        </p>

        <h2 class="policy-h1">HELP (HELP)</h2>
        <p>
            Reply <strong>HELP</strong> to any message to receive contact information for your
            campus manager. You may also contact us directly at the addresses below.
        </p>

        <h2 class="policy-h1">SUPPORTED CARRIERS</h2>
        <p>
            The SMS program is compatible with all major U.S. carriers. Carriers, including but
            not limited to AT&amp;T, T-Mobile, Verizon, and their respective MVNOs, are not liable
            for delayed or undelivered messages.
        </p>

        <h2 class="policy-h1">PRIVACY</h2>
        <p>
            Your mobile phone number is used only for the purposes described above. We do not
            sell, rent, or share your mobile number with third parties for marketing purposes.
            SMS delivery is handled by Microsoft Azure Communication Services, a third-party
            processor operating under a Data Processing Agreement. Additional detail is available
            in our SMS Consent Policy (NH-SMS-001).
        </p>

        <h2 class="policy-h1">CHANGES TO THESE TERMS</h2>
        <p>
            New Heights may update these Terms as the program evolves or as regulatory requirements
            change. Material changes will be communicated to staff through the Staff Portal and
            by email.
        </p>

        <h2 class="policy-h1">CONTACT</h2>
        <p>Questions about these Terms or the SMS program can be directed to:</p>
        <div class="consent-callout">
            New Heights Adult High School<br />
            Attn: Human Resources<br />
            Email: hr@newheightsed.com
        </div>

        <div class="signature-block">
            <div class="signature-line">
                <span class="sig-bar"></span>
                <span class="sig-label">Employee Signature</span>
            </div>
            <div class="signature-line">
                <span class="sig-bar"></span>
                <span class="sig-label">Date</span>
            </div>
        </div>

    </div>
</div>
